\b To create a new project file
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 1\tab In Help Workshop, click the File menu, and then click New.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 2\tab Double-click Help Project.
\par 3\tab Type the name of the project (.hpj) file, and then click OK.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \b Note
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\f1 \tab When you create a project file, Help Workshop configures the minimum settings you need to create a Help file. Before you can compile, however, you must click the Files button and specify at least one .rtf file.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
