\b To add copyright information
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 1\tab In Help Workshop, open the project (.hpj) file.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 2\tab Click Options.
\par 3\tab In the Copyright Information area, type the copyright information you want to display in the Version dialog box or when users paste or print Help text.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \b Notes
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\f1 \tab You can specify up to 255 characters of copyright information for the Version dialog box. There is no limit to the number of characters you can specify for the copyright information that appears when users paste or print Help text.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab If you add \b %date\plain\f1\fs16  at the end of the text you want to display in the Version dialog box, Help Workshop will substitute the current date whenever you compile the Help file.
