\b To include additional contents files
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 1\tab Open the main contents file, and then click the place where you want the information in the second contents file to appear.
\par 2\tab Click Add Above or Add Below, and then click Include.
\par 3\tab Type the name of the contents file that you want to include.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \b Notes
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\tab \f1 If the included contents file is not available when WinHelp initializes the Help file, the included file will be not appear on the Contents tab.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\tab \f1 A default Help filename specified in the included contents file affects only the included file, not the main contents file.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
