\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 1\tab In Help Workshop, open the contents (.cnt) file.
\par 2\tab Click the item above or below which you want to add a heading, and then click Add Above or Add Below.
\par 3\tab Click Heading, and then type the heading in the Title box.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \b Note
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\tab \f1 You can assign up to nine levels of headings and topics by using the Move Right and Move Left buttons.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL(`BAS_CNT_OVERVIEW;PRO_CNT_ADD_TOPIC')\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL(`BAS_CNT_OVERVIEW;PRO_CNT_ADD_TOPIC')}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:00c4}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} To add topics to the Contents tab}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} PRO_CNT_ADD_TOPIC}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} PRO_CNT;PRO_CNT_ADD_TOPIC}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} contents files;contents files, adding topics to the Contents tab;Contents tab;Contents tab, adding topics to;topic IDs;topic IDs, adding to contents files;topics,;topics, adding to the Contents tab}
\b To add topics to the Contents tab
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 1\tab In Help Workshop, open the contents (.cnt) file.
\par 2\tab Click the item above or below which you want to add a topic, and then click Add Above or Add Below.
\par 3\tab Click Topic, and then type a title in the Title box.
\par 4\tab In the Topic ID box, type the topic ID.
\par 5\tab If the topic is not in the default Help file, type the name of the file that contains the topic in the Help File box.
\par 6\tab If you want to display the topic in a window type other than the default window, specify the window in the Window Type box. The window you specify must be defined in the project (.hpj) file.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \b Notes
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\tab \f1 If you do not specify information in the Help File, WinHelp searches the default Help file for the topic. If you do not specify information in the Window Type box, WinHelp displays the topic in the window type specified in the default Help file.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\tab \f1 You can assign a macro to a topic instead of a topic ID. In the Topic ID box, type an exclamation point (!) followed by the macro. To separate multiple macros, use colons (:).
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL(`BAS_CNT_OVERVIEW;PRO_CNT_ADD_BOOK')\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL(`BAS_CNT_OVERVIEW;PRO_CNT_ADD_BOOK')}
\par \page
