\b To add another tab to the Help Topics dialog box
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 1\tab In Help Workshop, open the contents (.cnt) file.
\par 2\tab Click Tabs, and then click Add.
\par 3\tab In the Tab Name box, type the name you want to display on the tab.
\par 4\tab In the DLL Filename box, type the filename of the DLL that provides the dialog procedure to support the tab.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL(`new_tab;DLL_WRITE_OVERVIEW;BAS_CNT_OVERVIEW')\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL(`new_tab;DLL_WRITE_OVERVIEW;BAS_CNT_OVERVIEW')}
