{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} PRO_HPJ_COMPILE}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} PRO_HCW;PRO_HPJ_COMPILE}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} compiling;compiling, Help files;Help files;Help files, compiling;Help Workshop;Help Workshop, compiling Help files;project files;project files, compiling}
\b To compile a Help file
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 1\tab If the project file is already open in Help Workshop, save the file.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 2\tab Click the \ul Compile button.\plain\f1\fs16 {\v 22T9EAQ}
\par 3\tab In the Project File box, type the name and location of the project (.hpj) file you want to compile, and then click Compile.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \b Tips
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\f1 \tab You do not have to open a project file to compile it.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab If a project file is open, you can click the Save And Compile button to compile the file.
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab For information about the other settings in this dialog box, click \{bmc bm0.bmp\} at the top of the dialog box, and then click the setting.
