\b To compile more than one Help file at a time
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 1\tab Using a text editor, create an ASCII text file that lists the full path of each of your project files on a separate line. Specify the project files in the order in which you want Help Workshop to compile them.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 2\tab Save the file using the filename extension .hmk.
\par 3\tab Open Help Workshop, and then click \ul Compile button.\plain\f1\fs16 {\v 22T9EAQ}
\par 4\tab In the Project File box, type the name of your .hmk file, and then click Compile.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL(`BAS_ABOUT_HPJ_FILES;EXEC_HCW')\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL(`BAS_ABOUT_HPJ_FILES;EXEC_HCW')}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:00cc}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} To view a Help file from Help Workshop}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} PRO_RUN_HELP}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} PRO_HCW;PRO_RUN_HELP}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} Help files;Help files, viewing from Help Workshop;Help topics,;Help topics, viewing topics with mapped IDs;Help Workshop;Help Workshop, viewing Help files from;mapped topic IDs, viewing topics with;running Help files from Help Workshop;topic IDs;topic IDs, viewing topics with mapped IDs;topics,;topics, viewing topics with mapped IDs;viewing Help files from Help Workshop}
\b To view a Help file from Help Workshop
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 1\tab After you compile a Help file, click the \ul Run WinHelp\plain\f1\fs16 {\v 2T4V0QE} button.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 2\tab Specify the name of the Help file. 
\par 3\tab If you want to view topics whose IDs are mapped to numeric values in your project (.hpj) file, type the name and location of the project file and click Refresh.
\par 4\tab Click View Help.
