{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:0003}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} ALink macro}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} ALink}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} ALink;new_macro}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} AL macro;ALink macro;macros,;macros, ALink}
\b\fs24 ALink macro
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 ALink(\plain\f1\fs16 keyword[\b ;\'a0\plain\f1\fs16 keyword] [\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0type[\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0topic-ID [\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0window-name]]]\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Searches for keywords specified by A-footnotes.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\brdrb\brdrs\tx1575 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 keyword\tab Specifies one or more keywords to search for. Multiple keywords must be separated by a semicolon. If any keyword contains a comma, the entire keyword string must be enclosed in quotation marks.
\par type\tab Specifies the action to perform if one or more keywords are found. If this parameter is not specified or is zero, the default action is always to display the Topics Found dialog box containing the topic title. This parameter may specify one or more of the following values, separated by spaces.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li2875\ri125\fi-1295\brdrb\brdrs\tx2875\tx3145 \b Value\tab Meaning
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2875\ri125\fi-1295\tx2875\tx3145 \plain\f1\fs16 JUMP (1)\b \tab \plain\f1\fs16 Specifies that if only one topic matches any of the keywords, WinHelp should jump directly to that topic.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2875\ri125\fi-1295\tx1575\tx2875 TITLE (2)\tab Specifies that if a keyword is found in more than one Help file, WinHelp should display the title of the Help file (as specified in the contents [.cnt] file) beside the topic title in the Topics Found dialog box.
\par TEST (4)\tab Specifies that the macro should return a value indicating whether or not there is at least one match. The TestALink macro is converted by Help Workshop into an ALink macro with this parameter.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575\tx5035 topic-ID\tab Specifies the topic to display in a pop-up window if no matches are found. If this parameter is not specified, WinHelp displays a message box with the text \plain\f0\fs16 \'93\f1 No additional information is available\plain\f0\fs16 \'94\f1 . To specify a topic in a different Help file, the topic ID should end with an \plain\f0\fs16 \'91\f1 @\plain\f0\fs16 \'92\f1  character and the name of the Help file.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575\tx2965 window-name\tab Specifies the window type in which to display the topic. If this parameter is not specified, the window type that is specified for a topic (if one is defined) is used, or the default or current window is used. If this macro results in an interfile jump, the window type must be defined in the project file for the Help file that is being jumped to.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575\tx2965 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575\tx2965 \plain\f1\fs16 The ALink macro searches for A-keyword matches in the current Help file. If the Help file is associated with a contents file, WinHelp searches all Help files specified in the contents file (by the :Index and :Link commands) for matching A-keywords.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575\tx2965 The ALink macro is identical to the KLink macro except that it searches for A-keywords instead of K-keywords.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575\tx2965 Help Workshop automatically converts the ALink macro to AL, which is the only form of the macro that WinHelp can use.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575\tx2965 The ALink macro is new for WinHelp version 4.0.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575\tx2965 \b Examples
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575\tx2965 \plain\f1\fs16 The following example generates a list of topics that contain the \plain\f0\fs16 \'93\f1 network printing\plain\f0\fs16 \'94\f1  or \plain\f0\fs16 \'93\f1 local printing\plain\f0\fs16 \'94\f1  keywords in A-footnotes:
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab ALink(network printing;local printing)
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 The following example generates a list of topics that contain the keyword \plain\f0\fs16 \'93\f1 how_to\plain\f0\fs16 \'94\f1  in A-footnotes and displays those topics in the Steps window:
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab ALink(how_to, , , Steps)
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 The following example returns a value of \plain\f0\fs16 \'93\f1 1\plain\f0\fs16 \'94\f1  if at least one topic with the keyword \plain\f0\fs16 \'93\f1 saving\plain\f0\fs16 \'94\f1  is found:
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab ALink(saving, TEST)
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
