\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 BookmarkDefine()\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the Define dialog box, which is available from the Bookmark menu in a main Help window.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Parameters\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 This macro does not take any parameters.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 Bookmarks do not keep track of the window type the topic was originally displayed in. When you use the Bookmark menu or call the BookmarkMore macro, the bookmark topic is displayed in the current window type.
\par If the BookmarkDefine macro is run from a pop-up window, the bookmark is attached to the topic that invoked the pop-up window.
