\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 ChangeButtonBinding(\plain\f1\fs16 button-ID\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0button-macro\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Assigns a macro to a button bar button.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1595\ri125\fi-1445\brdrb\brdrs\tx1595 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1595\ri125\fi-1445\tx1595 button-ID\tab Specifies the identifier assigned to the button by the CreateButton macro, or for a standard Help button.
\par button-macro\tab Specifies the macro assigned to the button. Separate multiple macros using colons or semicolons. If multiple macros are specified in a project file, use colons.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1595 \b Comment
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1595 \plain\f1\fs16 Help Workshop automatically converts the ChangeButtonBinding macro to CBB.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1595 \b Example
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1595 \plain\f1\fs16 In the following macro, an ALink macro is assigned to a button whose ID is SeeAlso:
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab [CONFIG]\line
