\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 ChangeEnable(\plain\f1\fs16 button-ID\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0button-macro\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Assigns a macro to a button bar button and enables that button.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1595\ri125\fi-1445\brdrb\brdrs\tx1595 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1595\ri125\fi-1445\tx1595 button-ID\tab Specifies the identifier assigned to the button by the CreateButton macro, or for a standard Help button.
\par button-macro\tab Specifies the macro assigned to the button.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1595 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1595 \plain\f1\fs16 This macro is equivalent to calling both ChangeButtonBinding and EnableButton.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1595 Help Workshop automatically converts the ChangeEnable macro to CE, which is the only form of this macro that WinHelp can use.\b 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1595 \plain\f1\fs16 The ChangeEnable macro is new for WinHelp version 4.0.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1595 \b Example
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 In the following macro, an ALink macro is assigned to a button whose ID is SeeAlso:
