\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 ChangeItemBinding(\plain\f1\fs16 item-ID\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0item-macro\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Assigns a new macro to a WinHelp menu item.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\brdrb\brdrs\tx1575 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\tx1575 item-ID\tab Identifies the menu item. The ID must have been created with the AppendItem or InsertItem macros, or must be the ID for a standard WinHelp menu item.
\par item-macro\tab Specifies the Help macro or macro string to run when a user chooses the menu item. Separate multiple macros in a string using colons or semicolons.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Comments
