\b\fs24 DeleteMark macro
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 DeleteMark(\plain\f1\fs16 marker-text\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Removes a text marker added by using the SaveMark macro.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\brdrb\brdrs\tx1575 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\tx1575 marker-text\tab Specifies the text marker previously added by the SaveMark macro.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Comment
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 If the marker does not exist when the DeleteMark macro is run, WinHelp displays an error message.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Example
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 The following macro removes the marker \plain\f0\fs16 \'93\f1 Managing Memory\plain\f0\fs16 \'94\f1  from a Help file if the marker actually exists:
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab IfThen("Managing memory", DeleteMark(Managing Memory))
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \{button ,AL("MACRO_REF_TEXT_MARKER;macro_all;ifthen;SaveMark;GotoMark;IsMark;IsNotMark")\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL("MACRO_REF_TEXT_MARKER;macro_all;ifthen;SaveMark;GotoMark;IsMark;IsNotMark")}
