{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} DisableButton;MACROS_BTN}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} buttons,;buttons, disabling;DB macro;DisableButton macro;macros,;macros, DisableButton}
\b\fs24 DisableButton macro
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 DisableButton(\plain\f1\fs16 button-ID\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Disables (grays out) a button on the WinHelp button bar.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\brdrb\brdrs\tx1575 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\tx1575 button-ID\tab Specifies the standard button identifier or the identifier assigned to the button by the CreateButton macro.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 A button that is disabled by the DisableButton macro cannot be used in the topic until it is re-enabled by the EnableButton macro or re-activated by a user. For example, a disabled Contents, Index, or Help Topics button is re-enabled if a user clicks an interfile jump.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 Help Workshop automatically converts the DisableButton macro to DB.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
