\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} ExecFile;new_macro}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} EF macro;ExecFile macro;macros,;macros, ExecFile}
\b\fs24 ExecFile macro
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 ExecFile(\plain\f1\fs16 program[\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0arguments[\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0display-state[\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0topic-ID]]]\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Runs a program or the program associated with a file.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\brdrb\brdrs\tx1435 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 program\tab Specifies the name of the program to be run or the name of a file. If a file is specified, the program associated with that file type is started.
\par arguments\tab Specifies the command-line arguments to send to the program.
\par display-state\tab Specifies a value indicating how the program's window is to be shown. If this parameter is not specified, SW_SHOW is used (activates the window and shows it in its default size and position). This optional parameter can be one of the following values.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3595\ri125\fi-2155\brdrb\brdrs\tx3595 \b Value\tab Meaning
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3595\ri125\fi-2155\tx3595 \plain\f1\fs16 SW_HIDE\tab Hides the window.
\par SW_MINIMIZE\tab Minimizes the window.
\par SW_RESTORE\tab Restores the window to its original size and position if the window is minimized or maximized.
\par SW_SHOW\tab Activates the window and displays it in its current size and position.
\par SW_SHOWMAXIMIZED\tab Activates the window and maximizes it.
\par SW_SHOWMINIMIZED\tab Activates the window and displays it minimized.
\par SW_SHOWMINNOACTIVE\tab Displays the window minimized, but WinHelp keeps the focus.
\par SW_SHOWNA\tab Displays a window in its current state, but WinHelp keeps the focus. (If the window was minimized before this call, it will stay minimized.)
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3595\ri125\fi-2155\tx3595 SW_SHOWNOACTIVATE\tab Displays a window in its most recent size and position, but WinHelp keeps the focus.
\par SW_SHOWNORMAL\tab Activates and displays the window. If the window is minimized or maximized, Windows restores it to its original size and position (same as SW_RESTORE).
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 topic-ID\tab Specifies the ID of the topic to display if the specified file or program cannot be started.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \plain\f1\fs16 If a path is specified, WinHelp first searches for the file in the specified path. If the file is not found or no path was specified, WinHelp searches the same locations as it does when it searches for Help files:
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab The folder of the current Help file.
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab The current folder.
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab The System subfolder in the Windows folder.
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab The Windows folder.
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab The folders listed in the PATH environment.
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab The location specified in the Winhelp.ini file.
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab The Help portion of the registry.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 Help Workshop automatically converts the ExecFile macro to EF, which is the only form of this macro that WinHelp can use.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 The ExecFile macro is new for WinHelp version 4.0.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \b Example
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \plain\f1\fs16 The following example opens the WIN.INI file in the program associated with .ini files:
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab ExecFile(win.ini)
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
