{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} ExtAbleItem macro;macros,;macros, ExtAbleItem;menu items;menu items, enabling or disabling}
\b\fs24 ExtAbleItem macro
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 ExtAbleItem(\plain\f1\fs16 item-ID\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0display-state\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Enables or disables a menu item.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\brdrb\brdrs\tx1435 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 item-ID\tab Specifies the identifier assigned to the menu item by the AppendItem, ExtInsertItem, or InsertItem macro.
\par display-state\tab Specifies the state of the menu item. This parameter can be one of the following values:
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2875\ri125\fi-1435\brdrb\brdrs\tx2875 \b Value\tab Meaning
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2875\ri125\fi-1435\tx2875 \plain\f1\fs16 GRAYED\tab Disables (grays out) the menu item.
\par CHECKED\tab Places a check mark next to the menu item.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx2875 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx2875 \plain\f1\fs16 You cannot use this macro to change a standard WinHelp menu item.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx2875 WinHelp ignores this macro if it is run in a secondary window.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx2875 The ExtAbleItem macro is new for WinHelp version 4.0.
