{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} ExtInsertMenu macro;macros,;macros, ExtInsertMenu;menus;menus, inserting submenus in;submenus, inserting}
\b\fs24 ExtInsertMenu macro
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 ExtInsertMenu(\plain\f1\fs16 parent-ID\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0menu-ID\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0menu-name\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0menu-position[\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0display-state]\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Inserts a submenu in a previously defined menu.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1725\ri125\fi-1605\brdrb\brdrs\tx1725 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1725\ri125\fi-1595\tx1725 parent-ID\tab Specifies the name that WinHelp uses to identify the parent menu to which this submenu is added. For a custom menu, this parameter is the name that was used when the menu was created by the ExtInsertMenu or the InsertMenu macro.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1725\ri125\fi-1605\tx1725 menu-ID\tab Specifies the name that WinHelp uses internally to identify the menu. This identifier can be used by the AppendItem, ExtInsertItem or ExtInsertMenu macros to access to the menu.
\par menu-name\tab Specifies the name that WinHelp displays for this menu. An ampersand (&) before a character in the name identifies it as the menu's accelerator.
\par menu-position\tab Specifies the integer position on the menu bar of the new menu name. Position 0 is the first position.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1725\ri125\fi-1605\tx1705 display-state\tab Specifies the state of the menu item. This parameter may be one of the following values:
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3055\ri125\fi-1345\brdrb\brdrs\tx3055 \b Value\tab Meaning
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3055\ri125\fi-1345\tx3055 \plain\f1\fs16 CHECKED\tab Places a check mark next to the menu item.
\par GRAYED\tab Disables (grays out) the menu item.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3055 \b Comment
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3055 \plain\f1\fs16 WinHelp ignores this macro if it is run in a secondary window.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3055 \b Example
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3055 \plain\f1\fs16 The following macro adds a Wizard submenu to the standard Help menu:
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab ExtInsertMenu(mnu_help, mnu_wizard, &Wizard, 2)
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \{button ,AL("MACRO_REF_MENU;macro_all;ExtInsertItem;ExtAbleItem;AppendItem;InsertMenu;ResetMenu;REF_STD_MENU;CONFIG")\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL("MACRO_REF_MENU;macro_all;ExtInsertItem;ExtAbleItem;AppendItem;InsertMenu;ResetMenu;REF_STD_MENU;CONFIG")}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:0025}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} FileExist macro}
