\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 JumpContext(\plain\f1\fs16 [filename\b >\plain\f1\fs16 window-name\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 ]\'a0context-number\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Jumps to a topic identified by a context number.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1795\ri125\fi-1665\brdrb\brdrs\tx1795 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1795\ri125\fi-1665\tx1795 filename\tab Specifies the name of the destination file for the jump. This parameter is optional.
\par window-name\tab Specifies the window type in which to display the topic.
\par context-number\tab Specifies the \ul context number\plain\f1\fs16 {\v 2O07FH3} of the topic in the destination file. The context number must be defined in the [MAP] section of the project file.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1795 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1795 \plain\f1\fs16 The context number is identified by an entry in the\b  \plain\f1\fs16 [MAP] section of the project file.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1795 Help Workshop automatically converts the JumpContext macro to JC, which is the only form of this macro that WinHelp can use.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1795 \b Example
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1795 \plain\f1\fs16 The following macro jumps to the topic mapped to the context number 801 in the Progman.hlp file:
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab JumpContext(progman.hlp, 801)
