\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} DBCS;HPJ_REF;new_hpj;translate_hpj}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} character sets;character sets, double-byte (DBCS);DBCS option in OPTIONS section;double-byte character set;fonts,;fonts, DBCS character set;language IDs;project files;project files, DBCS option}
\b\fs24 DBCS
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 DBCS=\plain\f1\fs16 value
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 You specify the DBCS option in the [OPTIONS] section of the project (.hpj) file. DBCS specifies whether the files that will be compiled use a double-byte character set (DBCS).
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 Help Workshop recognizes certain language IDs (LCID option) and forces the DBCS option to a particular setting, no matter how you specify it in the project file. The following language IDs force DBCS=YES.
