{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} RB72W}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} FTS;HPJ_REF;new_hpj}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} FTS option in OPTIONS section;project files;project files, FTS option}
\b\fs24 FTS
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 FTS=\plain\f1\fs16 fts-value
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 You specify the FTS option in the [OPTIONS] section of the project (.hpj) file. FTS specifies what type of index file to create for the full-text search feature, which you can access using the Find tab in the Help Topics dialog box.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1625\ri125\fi-1495\brdrb\brdrs\tx1615 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1625\ri125\fi-1495\tx1615 fts-value\tab Specifies the level of information to include in the index file used by the full-text search engine. This value can be a sum of the following hex values.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li3065\ri125\fi-1435\brdrb\brdrs\tx3065 \b Hex Value\tab Meaning\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3065\ri125\fi-1435\tx3065 0x01\tab Create an index file for full-text searching.
\par 0x02\tab Include untitled topics (such as context-sensitive Help topics) in the index file.
\par 0x04\tab Include information to support phrase searching.
\par 0x08\tab Include information to provide feedback on phrase searches.
\par 0x10\tab Include information to support similarity searches.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3065 \b Comment
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3065 \plain\f1\fs16 The FTS option is new.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
