\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} HPJ_REF;INDEX_SEPARATORS;new_hpj;translate_hpj}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} INDEX_SEPARATORS option;project files;project files, INDEX_SEPARATORS option}
\b\fs24 INDEX_SEPARATORS
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 INDEX_SEPARATORS="\plain\f1\fs16 separators\b "\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 You specify the INDEX_SEPARATORS option in the [OPTIONS] section of the project file. INDEX_SEPARATORS identifies the characters WinHelp uses to delineate separate keyword entries.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1625\ri125\fi-1495\brdrb\brdrs\tx1615 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1625\ri125\fi-1495\tx1615 separators\tab Specifies the character used to separate keywords in an entry (for example, "keywords, entering") and the character used to separate entries in a list. If this option is not used, the default comma and colon values (",:") are used.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1615 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1615 \plain\f1\fs16 The INDEX_SEPARATORS option is new.
