\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} RB.LMD}
{\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} HPJ_REF;LCID;new_hpj;translate_hpj}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} LCID option in OPTIONS section;project files;project files, LCID option}
\b\fs24 LCID
\par \pard\keepn\keep\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 LCID=\plain\f1\fs16 language\'a0case-insensitive\'a0case-sensitive
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 You specify the LCID option in the [OPTIONS] section of the project file. LCID specifies the language of the Help file. This information is used when sorting keywords in the index, and determines what character to use for curly quotes.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1625\ri125\fi-1495\brdrb\brdrs\tx1615 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1625\ri125\fi-1495\tx1615 language\tab Specifies the hex value of the language on which to base sorting. This parameter can have only one value.
\par case-sensitive\tab Specifies the bit flags for ignoring non-spacing marks and symbols in case-sensitive text.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li3065\ri125\fi-1435\brdrb\brdrs\tx3065 \b Hex Value\tab Meaning\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3065\ri125\fi-1435\tx3065 0x2\tab Ignore non-spacing marks.
\par 0x4\tab Ignore punctuation.
\par 0x6\tab Ignore non-spacing marks and symbols.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1625\ri125\fi-1495\tx1615 case-insensitive\tab Specifies the bit flags for ignoring non-spacing marks and symbols in text that is not case-sensitive.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li3065\ri125\fi-1435\brdrb\brdrs\tx3065 \b Hex Value\tab Meaning\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3065\ri125\fi-1435\tx3065 0x2\tab Ignore non-spacing marks.
\par 0x4\tab Ignore punctuation.
\par 0x6\tab Ignore non-spacing marks and symbols.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3065 \b Comment
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3065 \plain\f1\fs16 The \b LCID\plain\f1\fs16  option is new.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
