{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:012d}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} >\{ewc\}, \{ewl\}, \{ewr\} statements}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} J8.L52}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} ewx}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} embedded windows;windows,;windows, embedded}
\b\fs24 \{\-ewc\'7d, \{\-ewl\'7d, \{\-ewr\'7d statements
\par \pard\keepn\keep\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 \{\-ew\plain\f1\fs16 x\b \'a0\plain\f1\fs16 DLL-name\b ,\'a0\plain\f1\fs16 window-name\b ,\'a0\plain\f1\fs16 data\b \'7d\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 The \{\-ewx\'7d reference creates an embedded window in the Help file.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\brdrb\brdrs\tx1575 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 x\tab Specifies how the graphic appears in the topic. The following characters can be specified:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\brdrb\brdrs\tx2165 \b Value\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2165\ri125\fi-555\tx2165 c\tab Aligns the window as a text character on the baseline of the type in exactly the same place in the paragraph where the reference occurs.
\par l\tab Aligns the window along the left margin.
\par r\tab Aligns the window along the right margin.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 DLL-name\tab Specifies the name of the DLL that controls the embedded window. The filename should not include an extension or be fully qualified. WinHelp will search for the file in the same locations as it searches for Help files.
\par window-name\tab Specifies the name of the embedded window class as defined in the source for the DLL.
\par data\tab Specifies an arbitrary string, which WinHelp passes to the embedded window when it creates the window. The DLL is responsible for parsing this string.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Example
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 The following shows an embedded window reference:
\par \pard\keep\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab \{\-ewl FADE, AmfWnd, clipbrd.amf\'7d
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL("embed_dll")\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL("embed_dll")}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:012e}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} \{mci\} statement}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} J8.SKN}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} mci}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} adding;adding, multimedia to topics;animation;animation, adding to topics;avi files in Help topics;files,;files, .avi;mci statement;multimedia;multimedia, adding to topics;sound, adding to topics;video, adding to topics}
\b\fs24 \{\-mci\'7d statement
\par \pard\keepn\keep\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 \{\-mci\plain\f1\fs16 [\b _left\plain\f1\fs16  | \b _right\plain\f1\fs16 ]\b \'a0\plain\f1\fs16 [options\b ,\plain\f1\fs16 ]\'a0filename\b \'7d\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 The \b \{\-mci\'7d\plain\f1\fs16  command inserts an .avi file into a topic.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\brdrb\brdrs\tx1575 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 options\tab Specifies the options for the multimedia control window that is created. Use spaces (not commas) to specify more than one option.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li2805\ri125\fi-1215\brdrb\brdrs\tx2805 \b Value\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2805\ri125\fi-1215\tx2805 EXTERNAL\tab Keeps the file outside of the Help file.
\par NOPLAYBAR\tab No playbar is shown (useful for auto-play and repeat).
\par NOMENU\tab No menu button is shown if there is a playbar.
\par REPEAT\tab The file automatically repeats when play is done.
\par PLAY\tab The file automatically plays when shown.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 filename\tab Specifies the name of the multimedia file to include in the topic.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 For WinHelp version 4.0, use this command only with .avi files. Future versions will support other multimedia formats.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 If no options are specified, a playbar appears with a menu button, and the file is not played until the user requests it.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Examples
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 The following command creates a multimedia control window that automatically plays the file demo.avi when the topic is shown:
\par \pard\keep\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab \{\-mci PLAY, demo.avi\'7d
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL("BAS_ADDING_VIDEO;BAS_ADDING_SOUND;MM_DESIGN;TMPDIR")\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL("BAS_ADDING_VIDEO;BAS_ADDING_SOUND;MM_DESIGN;TMPDIR")}
