{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:012f}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} HCRTF command-line switches}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} EXEC_HCRTF}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} EXEC_HCRTF}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} command-line switches;compiling;compiling, from a command line;HCRTF command-line switches;Hcrtf.exe;Help Workshop;Help Workshop, command-line options}
\b\fs24 HCRTF command-line switches
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 HCRTF\'a0\plain\f1\fs16 [\b /B\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0path]\'a0[\b /O\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0HLP-filename]\'a0[\b /X\plain\f1\fs16 [\b CHNRT\plain\f1\fs16 ]]\'a0[RTF-filename]\'a0[\b /NC\plain\f1\fs16 ]\'a0[\b /XT\plain\f1\fs16 ]\'a0[HPJ-filename]
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 The Hcrtf.exe program is used to compile a Help file, test a contents file, or provide information about an existing Help file. It is called automatically by the Hcw.exe program. If you run Hcrtf.exe directly, you can use the following switches:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\brdrb\brdrs\tx1575 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 \b /A\tab \plain\f1\fs16 Specifies that additional information is to be added to the Help file. For version 4.0, the additional information is the topic ID of each topic and the source file the topic appears in. If the Help Author command on the File menu in Help Workshop is checked, you can display this information by clicking a topic using your right mouse button, and then clicking Topic Information.\b 
\par /B\plain\f1\fs16  path\tab Specifies the path to search for bitmaps. You can specify multiple paths with multiple /B switches.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 \b /F(C|D|F|G|H|I)\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Specifies a report command. You must use one of the listed parameters with this switch. The switch and its parameter must be followed by a space, the Help filename, another space, and the fully qualified path of the output filename. The /F switch should always be used in conjunction with a /X switch. Specify one of the following parameters with the /F switch.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li2805\ri125\fi-1215\brdrb\brdrs\tx2805 \b Value\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2805\ri125\fi-1215\tx2805 \b C\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Writes all the topic titles in the Help file to the output file.
\par \b D\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Writes all the topic text in the Help file to the output file.
\par \b F\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Writes all the hash numbers in the Help file to the output file.
\par \b G\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Writes project file information in the Help file to the output file.
\par \b H\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Writes all K-keywords in the Help file to the output file.
\par \b I\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Writes all A-keywords in the Help file to the output file.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 \b /O\plain\f1\fs16  HLP-filename\tab Specifies the name of the Help file to create. Use this switch only if you are not compiling an .HPJ file.
\par \b /N\plain\f1\fs16 [\b CGW\plain\f1\fs16 ]\tab Specifies an option to turn off.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li2805\ri125\fi-1215\brdrb\brdrs\tx2805 \b Value\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2805\ri125\fi-1215\tx2805 \b C\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Turns off compression, no matter what value is specified by the COMPRESS option in the project file.
\par \b G\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Prevents the animation window from appearing.
\par \b W\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Prevents the automatic creation of a window definition, if a window specified in a hotspot or macro was not defined in the project file.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 
\par \b /X\plain\f1\fs16 [\b CHNRT\plain\f1\fs16 ]\tab Specifies that there is no parent to send messages to. You can include one or more of the following parameters with the \b /X\plain\f1\fs16  switch, provided they are not separated by spaces.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li2805\ri125\fi-1215\brdrb\brdrs\tx2805 \b Value\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2805\ri125\fi-1215\tx2805 \b C\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Specifies that Help Workshop should compile the RTF text on the Clipboard. This switch works only if a text editor has registered the "Rich Text Format" Clipboard format. This switch cannot be used if the /XR switch is used.
\par \b H\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Specifies that, when the compile is complete, the Help file is to be displayed in WinHelp.
\par \b N\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Specifies that the progress window should not be shown.
\par \b R\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Specifies that an .rtf file is being used instead of a project file. You cannot use this switch with the /XC switch. After all other possible switches have been specified, type one or more spaces and the name of the .rtf file.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2805\ri125\fi-1215\tx2805 \b T\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Specifies that there are no errors in the .rtf file. Some error checking will be turned off to speed up the compilation process. This switch should be used only when compilation speed is crucial. 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 RTF-filename\tab Specifies the name of the .rtf file to process. Used only when /XR has been specified.
\par HPJ-filename\tab If neither the /XC or /XR switch is specified, the file is presumed to be a project file.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Example
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 The following example would compile the Myfile.rtf topic file, producing the Test.hlp Help file for display in WinHelp:
\par \pard\keep\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab hcrtf\'a0-o\'a0c:\'5ctmp\'5ctest.hlp -xhr\'a0myfile.rtf
\par \pard\sb45\sl-115\li295\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb25\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 \{button ,KL("HCW command;compiling, multiple Help files;COMPRESS option")\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!KL("HCW command;compiling, multiple Help files;COMPRESS option")}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:0130}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} HCW command}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} EXEC_HCW}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} EXEC_HCW}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} command-line switches;compiling;compiling, from a command line;HCW command;Help Workshop;Help Workshop, command-line options}
\b\fs24 HCW command
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 HCW\'a0\plain\f1\fs16 [[\b /C\plain\f1\fs16 ]\'a0[\'a0\b /M\plain\f1\fs16 ]\'a0[\b /E\plain\f1\fs16 ]\'a0[\b /N\plain\f1\fs16 ]]\'a0[\b /T\plain\f1\fs16 ]\'a0[filename]
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 The Hcw.exe program provides an interface to the Hcrtf.exe program.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\brdrb\brdrs\tx1575 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 \b /A\tab \plain\f1\fs16 Specifies that additional information is to be added to the Help file. For version 4.0, the additional information is the topic ID of each topic and the source file the topic appears in. If the Help Author command on the File menu in Help Workshop is checked, you can display this information by clicking a topic using your right mouse button, and then clicking Topic Information.\b 
\par /C\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Starts compiling the specified project (.hpj) file or \ul Help makefile (.hmk).\plain\f1\fs16 {\v B6EHF_}
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 \b /E\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Quits the Hcw.exe program after compiling the specified file. Use this switch in conjunction with the /C or /M switch.
\par \b /M\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Minimizes the Hcw.exe program while compiling the specified project file.
\par \b /N\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Turns off compression when compiling the specified file, no matter what value is specified for the COMPRESS option in the project file(s).
\par \b /R\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Specifies that the Help file is to be displayed in WinHelp as soon as it is compiled.\b 
\par /T\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Turns on Translation mode. This limits what can be changed in a contents (.cnt) or project file. Only text that should be translated to another language can be changed. This can also be set by clicking the Translation command on Help Workshop\plain\f0\fs16 \'92\f1 s File menu.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 filename\tab Specifies the name of one or more project, Help makefile, or contents files to open or compile.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Example
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 The following command compiles the New.hpj project file with no compression, minimizing the window while compiling, and adding additional information to the Help file:
\par \pard\keep\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab hcw /c /m /n /a\'a0new
