{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} winhelp_exe}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} command-line switches;WinHelp,;WinHelp, command-line switches;Winhlp32.exe command-line switches}
\b\fs24 Winhlp32.exe command-line switches
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 winhlp32.exe\'a0\plain\f1\fs16 [[\b -H\plain\f1\fs16 ]\'a0[\b -G\plain\f1\fs16 [n]]\'a0[\b -W\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0window-name]\'a0[\b -K\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0keyword]\'a0[\b -N\'a0\plain\f1\fs16 context-num]\'a0[\b -I\'a0\plain\f1\fs16 topic-id]\'a0[\b -P\plain\f1\fs16 \'a0pop-up-id]\'a0HLP-filename]
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 You can use the following switches may be used when starting WinHelp:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1455\brdrb\brdrs\tx1575 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 \b -G\plain\f1\fs16 [n]\tab Creates a configuration (.gid) file and quits. If a number is specified, it determines which extensible tab to display by default the first time the Help file is opened. A value of 1 would be the first tab beyond the Find tab.
\par \b -H\plain\f1\fs16 \tab Displays the Winhlp32.hlp Help file.
\par \b -I\plain\f1\fs16  topic-id\tab Displays the Help topic with the specified the topic ID.
\par \b -K \plain\f1\fs16 keyword\tab Displays the topic identified by the specified keyword.\b 
\par -N \plain\f1\fs16 context-num\tab Displays the topic specified by the \ul context number\plain\f1\fs16 {\v 2O07FH3} (defined in the [MAP] section of the project file).
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1575\ri125\fi-1445\tx1575 \b -P\plain\f1\fs16  pop-up-id\tab Displays the specified pop-up topic. You must use the -P switch in combination with the -I or -N switch, as shown in the following examples:
\par \tab WINHLP32 -P -I EXEC_WINHELP HCW.HLP
\par \tab WINHLP32 -P -N 311 MYFILE.HLP
\par \b -W\plain\f1\fs16  window-name\tab Displays the topic in the specified window definition.
\par HLP-filename\tab Specifies the Help file to display. If a name is not specified, the File Open dialog box appears.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 In Windows 95, the executable file for Winhelp has been renamed from Winhelp.exe to Winhlp32.exe. For backward compatibility reasons, Winhelp.exe still exists, but it now contains only the information necessary to start the Winhlp32.exe program.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 The -G switch should be used by Setup programs when they install a newer version of a Help file or a \ul contents file.\plain\f1\fs16 {\v 2GB40S} This switch causes the .gid file to be rebuilt. WinHelp will automatically build the .gid file the first time a Help file is opened \plain\f0\fs16 \'97\f1  unless the winhelp -g command has already been run on the file.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \b Example
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1575 \plain\f1\fs16 The following example displays the topic identified by content number 12 in a pop-up. This would be typically be used when registering a What\plain\f0\fs16 \'92\f1 s This verb for a file extension:
\par \pard\keep\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \tab winhlp32 -p -n12 myhelp
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL("GID")\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL("GID")}
\par \page
