{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} 3CSZ04P}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} FTS_phrase_compress;GetPhraseTable}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} GetPhraseTable function}
\b\fs24 GetPhraseTable
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 ERRORCODE GetPhraseTable(HCOMPRESSOR hcmp, PUINT pcPhrases, PBYTE *ppbImages, PUINT pcbImages, PBYTE *ppacbImageCompressed, PUINT pcbCompressed);
\par Retrieves the phrase table for the given compressor.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li2155\ri125\fi-2025\brdrb\brdrs\tx2155 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2155\ri125\fi-2025\tx2155 hcmp\tab Handle of the compressor. Must have been previously created using the \b NewCompressor\plain\f1\fs16  function.
\par pcPhrases\tab Address of the variable that receives the count of phrases in the table.
\par ppbImages\tab Address of a variable which will be set to the address of a buffer containing the phrase images. That buffer is allocated with malloc. Assume that the caller will free the buffer.
\par pcbImages\tab Address of the variable that receives the size in bytes of the *ppbImages data.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li2155\ri125\fi-2025\tx2155 ppacbImageCompressed\tab Address of a variable which will be set to the address of a buffer containing the phrase size information. That buffer is allocated with malloc. Assume that the caller will free the buffer.
\par pcbCompressed\tab Address of the variable that receives the size in bytes of the *ppacbImageCompressed data.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx2155 \b Return Value
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx2155 \plain\f1\fs16 Returns 0 if successful; an error value otherwise.
