\b\fs24 NewIndex
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 HINDEX NewIndex(const PBYTE pbSourceName, UINT uiTime1, UINT uiTime2, UINT iCharsetDefault, UINT lcidDefault, UINT fdwOptions);
\par Creates a full-text-search index that supports the types of searches specified by the fdwOptions parameters. Entries can be added to the index by using the \b ScanTopicTitle\plain\f1\fs16  and \b ScanTopicText\plain\f1\fs16  functions.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\brdrb\brdrs\tx1435 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 pbSourceName\tab Address of a null-terminated string specifying the name of the file (or text source) for which the index file is being created.
\par uiTime1\tab Low 32-bits of the 64-bit value identifying the creation date and time of the index.
\par uiTime2\tab High 32-bits of the 64-bit value identifying the creation date and time of the index.
\par iCharsetDefault\tab Default character set index for compression. Can be one of these values:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li3425\ri125\fi-1985\brdrb\brdrs\tx3415 \b Value\tab \plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3425\ri125\fi-1985\tx3415 ANSI_CHARSET\tab 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 lcidDefault\tab Default locale for the index. Can be any valid locale identifier.
\par fdwOptions\tab Type of index to create or action to take. Can be a combination of these values:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li3425\ri125\fi-1985\brdrb\brdrs\tx3415 \b Value\tab Meaning\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3425\ri125\fi-1985\tx3415 TOPIC_SEARCH\tab Can search for topics containing a given word or combination of words. If no other option is given, this option is required.
\par PHRASE_SEARCH\tab Can search for topics containing a given phrase or combination of phrases.
\par PHRASE_FEEDBACK\tab Can provide feedback about the validity of a phrase before carrying out a search. As the user constructs a phrase, the full-text engine can list the words that the user can type next to create a valid phrase. This option is valid only if PHRASE_SEARCH is also given.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3425\ri125\fi-1985\tx3415 VECTOR_SEARCH\tab Can search for topics that are similar. Similarity is based on the use and frequency of words in the topics. This option is valid only if both PHRASE_SEARCH and PHRASE_FEEDBACK are also given.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3415 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx3415 \plain\f1\fs16 The following values are define how topics are displayed:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1795\ri125\fi-1665\brdrb\brdrs\tx1795 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1795\ri125\fi-1665\tx1795 WINHELP_INDEX\tab Not used.
\par USE_VA_ADDR\tab Send MSG_FTS_JUMP_VA message to get a topic displayed.
\par USE_QWORD_JUMP\tab Send MSG_FTS_JUMP_QWORD message to get a topic displayed.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1795 If neither USE_VA_ADDR nor USE_QWORD_JUMP is part of fdwOptions, the MSG_FTS_JUMP_HASH message will be used to display topics.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1795 \b Return Value
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1795 \plain\f1\fs16 Returns the handle of the index if successful; NULL otherwise.
