{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:0156}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} ScanDisplayText function}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} _EWUUE}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} FTS_topic_hiliting;ScanDisplayText}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} ScanDisplayText function}
\b\fs24 ScanDisplayText
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 ERRORCODE ScanDisplayText(HHILITER hHiliter, BYTE* pbText, int cbText, UINT iCharset, LCID lcid);
\par This function supplies the display text for which hilite information is to be computed.  It may be called repeatedly to pass across the relevant display text. This is necessary when the text is composed of segments with different Charsets and/or Locales.\f5\fs22 
\par \f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\brdrb\brdrs\tx1435 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 hHiliter\tab Handle of the hiliter. Must have been previously created using the \b NewHiliter\plain\f1\fs16  function.
\par pbText\tab Address of the buffer containing the text to be scanned.
\par cbText\tab Size in bytes of the text.
\par iCharset\tab Character set of the text to be compressed. If this parameter is USE_DEFAULT, the function uses the default character set specified when the compressor was created.
\par  lcid\tab Locale identifier of the text to scan. If this parameter is USE_DEFAULT, the function uses the default locale specified when the index was created.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \b Return Value
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \plain\f1\fs16 Returns 0 if successful; an error value otherwise.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
