{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:0159}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} ScanTopicTitle function}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} 1J9SVS2}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} FTS_Index_Construct;ScanTopicTitle}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} ScanTopicTitle function}
\b\fs24 ScanTopicTitle
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 ERRORCODE ScanTopicTitle(HINDEX hinx, PBYTE pbTitle, UINT cbTitle, UINT iTopic, HANDLE hTopic, UINT iCharset, UINT lcid);
\par Begins a new topic and defines a title and handle values for the topic. The title text is internally passed to \b ScanTopicText\plain\f1\fs16 , and is considered part of the topic text during search transactions.
\par Subsequent calls to \b ScanTopicText\plain\f1\fs16  are associated with this topic until another call to \b ScanTopicTitle\plain\f1\fs16  or a call to \b SaveIndex\plain\f1\fs16 .
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\brdrb\brdrs\tx1435 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 hinx\tab Handle of an index to add the topic to. Must have been previously created using the \b NewIndex\plain\f1\fs16  function.
\par pbTitle\tab Address of the buffer containing the title of the topic. The text can be any combination of words and punctuation.
\par cbTitle\tab Size in bytes of the title.
\par iTopic\tab The high 32 bits of a 64-bit value which will identify this topic. This value is relevant when the USE_QWORD_JUMP option has been set at index creation time.
\par hTopic\tab The low 32 bits of a 64-bit value which will identify this topic.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 iCharset\tab Character set of the title text. If this parameter is USE_DEFAULT, the function uses the default character set specified when the index was created.
\par lcid\tab Locale identifier of the title text. If this parameter is USE_DEFAULT, the function uses the default locale specified when the index was created.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \b Return Value
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \plain\f1\fs16 Returns 0 if successful; an error value otherwise.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL("ScanTopicText;SaveIndex;NewIndex;fts_errorcode")\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL("ScanTopicText;SaveIndex;NewIndexfts_errorcode")}
\par \page
