\par \page
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} 1E0XAGK}
\pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Provides a place for you to type the ID of the topic that WinHelp displays whenever the user initiates a jump to a topic that is unavailable. For Help files that do not have an associated contents (.cnt) file, WinHelp displays the default topic as the first topic when the user first opens the Help file and when the Contents button is clicked. If you do not specify a default topic, WinHelp uses the first topic of the first file listed in the project (.hpj) file.
\par \page
