\par \page
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} 9SMYOB}
\pard\sb75\sl-235\li85\ri125 Lists topic IDs that are mapped to numeric values. If you want a program to call a Help topic directly (as in the case of context-sensitive Help), you must map the topic ID to a numeric value. The program passes this value to WinHelp to display the associated topic.
\par \page
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} J8_TQ_}
\pard\sb75\sl-235\li85\ri125 Click this to add a topic ID and its associated numeric value to the list.
\par \page
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} 240WDVW}
