\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Changing a window's background color
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 You can specify the background color of a window by opening your project (.hpj) file in Help Workshop, and then clicking the Windows button. Background color settings are on the Color tab. 
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Tip
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\f1 \tab For help on an item in the Window Properties dialog box, click \{bmc bm0.bmp\} in its title bar, and then click the item.
