\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 You can add buttons to or remove them from a window's button bar by opening your project (.hpj) file in Help Workshop, clicking the Windows button, and then clicking the Buttons tab. 
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Notes
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\f1 \tab For help on an item in the Window Properties dialog box, click \{bmc bm0.bmp\} in its title bar, and then click the item.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab In addition to the buttons provided by Help Workshop, you can also use Help macros to add up to 22 buttons to the button bar in a Help window. For more information, click Related Topics below.
