\par \page
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} .SVEAR}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Changing the main window's menu commands
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 You can add menus and menu commands to the menu bar in a main window by adding the necessary macros to the configuration section of your project (.hpj) file. To do this, open your project file in Help Workshop and click the Config button.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Tip
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\f1 \tab For help on an item in the Configuration Macros dialog box, click \{bmc bm0.bmp\} in its title bar, and then click the item.
