{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} 16Z.AQ0}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Considerations for writing pop-up topics
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 When you write pop-up topics, you may want to consider the following:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Unless you include an authorable Print button in pop-ups, users can print them only by clicking them with their right mouse button, and then clicking Print.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Topics that do not have titles specified by $ footnotes are typically excluded from the \ul full-text search\plain\f1\fs16 {\v ATV8VK} index. Because pop-ups are best used in context, it would be more confusing than helpful if users were able to find the text in them.
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab For context-sensitive Help topics that will be called from a program, make sure the first four characters in the topic ID are IDH_. This enables Help Workshop to detect whether topic IDs are mapped to numeric values in your project (.hpj) file.
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:0090}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} Guidelines for using video and animation}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} MM_DESIGN}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} DESIGN;MM_DESIGN}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} animation;animation, guidelines for using;avi files in Help topics;file size;Help system;Help system, multimedia guidelines;multimedia;multimedia, guidelines for using;video;video, guidelines for using}
\b Guidelines for using video and animation
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 Video and animation files can be included in any topic, including pop-up topics. WinHelp version 4.0 creates an embedded window for multimedia files and automatically sizes the window to accommodate the image or controller (if any). If the window is not large enough to display the controller, WinHelp crops the right and bottom edges. Users can resize the window to show any part of the controller that does not initially appear in the window.
\par Multimedia files tend to be large and can significantly increase a Help file's size. If your Help file is likely to be copied to a user's hard disk (rather than run from a CD-ROM), file size might be a an issue.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Note
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \plain\f2\fs16 \'b7\f1 \tab You can ship multimedia files without including them in your Help file. This feature may be useful if you want to run sample files that are already included as part of the product, or that currently exist on a user's computer.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL(`BAS_OVERVIEW;BAS_ADDING_VIDEO;BAS_ADDING_SOUND;TMPDIR;mci;PRO_ADD_VIDEO')\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL(`BAS_OVERVIEW;BAS_ADDING_VIDEO;BAS_ADDING_SOUND;TMPDIR;mci;PRO_ADD_VIDEO')}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:0091}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} Designing an index}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} INDEX_DESIGN}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} DESIGN;INDEX_DESIGN}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} Help system;Help system, designing an index;index entries, creating;index,;index, designing;index, guidelines for writing keywords;keywords;keywords, guidelines for writing;K-keywords;second-level index entries;topic keywords}
\b Designing an index
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 A comprehensive \ul keyword\plain\f1\fs16 {\v 9ML77Q} list is one of the most helpful navigating tools you can provide for users. In an index, you can provide synonyms that help users find information without requiring them to be familiar with your terminology. Even though WinHelp 4.0 supports \ul full-text search\plain\f1\fs16 {\v ATV8VK} features, you will probably want to prepare a keyword list. If users have only a full-text search index available to them, they can search for and find only words that are actually present in the text of the Help file.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \uldb \{bmc bm23.bmp\} Types of keywords\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %8DAFB1}
\par \uldb \{bmc bm23.bmp\} Keyword guidelines\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %BDO.1Y}
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL(`PRO_ADD_KEYWORD;PRO_ADD_LEVEL2_KEYWORDS;PRO_CNT_COMBINE_HELP_FILES')\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL(`PRO_ADD_KEYWORD;PRO_ADD_LEVEL2_KEYWORDS;PRO_CNT_COMBINE_HELP_FILES')}
\par \page
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} 8DAFB1}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Types of keywords
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 It is typically best to include several types of keywords in each topic. When you specify keywords, you may want to include:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Nontechnical terms that are likely to occur to beginning users
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Technical terms that are likely to occur to advanced users
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Common synonyms for technical terms
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Words that describe the topic generally
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Words that describe specific subjects within the topic
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Inverted forms of keyword phrases. For example, "combining Help files" and "Help files, combining"
\par \page
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} BDO.1Y}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b Keyword guidelines
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 If you want your index to look similar to those in Windows\'a095 Help, you may want to consider the following:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Always use the gerund form of verbs for keywords that begin with a verb
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Always use the plural form of nouns
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Use synonyms consistently throughout a family of Help files
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Make sure that keyword phrases beginning with the same word are consistently general or consistently specific
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 You can create first and \ul second-level index entries.\plain\f1\fs16 {\v DOQEEK} Users can either double-click second-level index entries to view particular topics or double-click a first-level entry to display the titles of all subentries in the Topics Found dialog box.
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:0092}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} Designing Help windows}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} WINDOW_DESIGN}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} tables}
\pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} DESIGN;WINDOW_DESIGN}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} Help system;Help system, designing Help windows;Help windows;Help windows, designing;secondary windows;secondary windows, designing;windows,;windows, designing}
\b Designing Help windows
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 When considering what type of information should go in \ul main\plain\f1\fs16 {\v O8.Q2} and \ul secondary windows,\plain\f1\fs16 {\v 2ZK4PT} consider the following features and limitations of each window type:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Secondary windows do not have a menu bar.
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab Secondary windows do not provide access to a history window or to bookmarks.
\par \f2 \'b7\f1 \tab You cannot automatically size the main window to accommodate the amount of text in a topic.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx295 If you are keeping your Help window on top, consider its size and placement. Ideally, users should be able to simultaneously read and carry out a procedure.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL(`BAS_OVERVIEW;BAS_HPJ_CREATE_WINDOW')\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL(`BAS_OVERVIEW;BAS_HPJ_CREATE_WINDOW')va}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:00e4}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} HELPINFO structure}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} HELPINFO}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} CS_HLP}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} context-sensitive Help;context-sensitive Help, structure containing information about requested item;HELPINFO structure;HELPINFO_MENUITEM parameter;HELPINFO_WINDOW parameter;reference;reference, WinHelp APIs}
\b\fs24 HELPINFO
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-195\li115\ri125\tx355 \plain\f1\fs16 typedef  struct  tagHELPINFO \{\-  \tab // hi\line
    UINT   cbSize;\line
    int    iContextType\line
    int    iCtrlId;\line
    HANDLE hItemHandle;\line
    DWORD  dwContextId;\line
    POINT  MousePos;\line
\'7d HELPINFO, FAR *LPHELPINFO;
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx355 The \b HELPINFO\plain\f1\fs16  structure contains information about an item for which context-sensitive Help has been requested.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\brdrb\brdrs\tx1435 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 cbSize\tab Size of this structure, in bytes.
\par iContextType\tab Type of context for which Help is requested. This member can be one of these values:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li3425\ri125\fi-1985\brdrb\brdrs\tx3415 \b Value\tab Meaning\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3425\ri125\fi-1985\tx3415 HELPINFO_MENUITEM\tab Help requested for a menu item.
\par HELPINFO_WINDOW\tab Help requested for a control or window.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 iCtrlld\tab Identifier of the window or control if the iContextType parameter is HELPINFO_WINDOW, or identifier of the menu item if the iContextType parameter is HELPINFO_MENUITEM.
\par hItemHandle\tab Identifier of the child window or control if iContextType is HELPINFO_WINDOW, or identifier of the associated menu if iContextType is HELPINFO_MENUITEM.
\par dwContextId\tab Help context identifier of the window or control.
\par MousePos\tab A \b POINT\plain\f1\fs16  structure that contains the screen coordinates of the mouse cursor. This parameter is useful for providing Help based on the position of the mouse cursor.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,KL("WM_HELP message;POINT")\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!KL("WM_HELP message;POINT")}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:00e5}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} HELPWININFO structure}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} HELPWININFO}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} HELPWININFO structure;reference;reference, WinHelp APIs;windows,;windows, structure containing size and position}
\b\fs24 HELPWININFO
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-195\li115\ri125\tx355 \plain\f1\fs16 typedef struct \{\-    \tab // hwi \line
    int   wStructSize;\line
    int   x;\line
    int   y;\line
    int   dx;\line
    int   dy;\line
    int   wMax;\line
    TCHAR rgchMember[2];\line
\'7d HELPWININFO;
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx355 The \b HELPWININFO\plain\f1\fs16  structure contains the size and position of either a primary or a secondary Help window.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\brdrb\brdrs\tx1435 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 wStructSize\tab Size of this structure, in bytes.
\par x\tab X-coordinate of the upper left corner of the window, in screen coordinates.
\par y\tab Y-coordinate of the upper left corner of the window, in screen coordinates.
\par dx\tab Width of the window, in pixels.
\par dy\tab Height of the window, in pixels.
\par wMax\tab Value specifying how to show the window. This member must be one of these values:
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li3595\ri125\fi-2125\brdrb\brdrs\tx3595 \b Value\tab Meaning\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3595\ri125\fi-2125\tx3595 SW_HIDE\tab Hides the window and passes activation to another window.
\par SW_MINIMIZE\tab Minimizes the specified window and activates the top-level window in the Z order.
\par SW_RESTORE\tab Same as SW_SHOWNORMAL.
\par SW_SHOW\tab Activates a window and displays it in its current size and position.
\par SW_SHOWMAXIMIZED\tab Activates the window and displays it as a maximized window.
\par SW_SHOWMINIMIZED\tab Activates the window and displays it as an icon.
\par SW_SHOWMINNOACTIVE\tab Displays the window as an icon. The window that is currently active remains active.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li3595\ri125\fi-2125\tx3595 SW_SHOWNA\tab Displays the window in its current state. The window that is currently active remains active.
\par SW_SHOWNOACTIVATE\tab Displays a window in its most recent size and position. The window that is currently active remains active.
\par SW_SHOWNORMAL\tab Activates and displays the window. Whether the window is minimized or maximized, Windows restores it to its original size and position.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 rgchMember\tab Name of the window.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \plain\f1\fs16 WinHelp divides the display into 1024 units in both the x- and y-directions. To create a secondary window that fills the upper left quadrant of the display, for example, a program would specify zero for the \b x\plain\f1\fs16  and \b y\plain\f1\fs16  members and 512 for the \b dx\plain\f1\fs16  and \b dy\plain\f1\fs16  members.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 A program can set the size and position information by calling the \b WinHelp\plain\f1\fs16  function with the HELP_SETWINPOS value.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL(`winhelp_api')\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL(`winhelp_api')}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:00e6}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} MULTIKEYHELP structure}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} MULTIKEYHELP}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up A}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up A} wh}
{\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} keywords;keywords, structure specifying table, associated keyword;MULTIKEYHELP structure;reference;reference, WinHelp APIs}
\b\fs24 MULTIKEYHELP
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx355 \plain\f1\fs16 typedef struct tagMULTIKEYHELP \{\- \tab // mkh \line
    DWORD mkSize;\line
    BYTE  mkKeylist;\line
    TCHAR szKeyphrase[1];\line
\'7d MULTIKEYHELP;
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx355 The \b MULTIKEYHELP\plain\f1\fs16  structure specifies a keyword table and an associated keyword to be used by the WinHelp program.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\brdrb\brdrs\tx1435 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 mkSize\tab Size of this structure, in bytes.
\par mkKeylist\tab A single character that identifies the keyword table to search.
\par szKeyphrase\tab A null-terminated text string that specifies the keyword to locate in the keyword table.
\par \pard\sl-115\li265\ri125\fi-185\brdrb\brdrs\tx295 
\par \pard\sb45\sl-235\li295\ri125\fi-185\tx295 \{button ,AL(`winhelp_api')\} \uldb Related Topics\plain\f1\fs16 {\v %!AL(`winhelp_api')}
\par \page
{\up +}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up +} BROWSE0027:00e7}
{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} WinHelp function}
{\up #}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up #} WinHelp}
{\up >}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up >} main}
\pard\keepn\sb115\sa115\sl-235\li115\ri125 {\up K}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up K} API, WinHelp;HELP_COMMAND command;HELP_CONTENTS command;HELP_CONTEXT command;HELP_CONTEXTMENU command;HELP_CONTEXTPOPUP command;HELP_FINDER command;HELP_FORCEFILE command;HELP_HELPONHELP command;HELP_INDEX command;HELP_KEY command;HELP_MULTIKEY command;HELP_PARTIALKEY command;HELP_QUIT command;HELP_SETCONTENTS command;HELP_SETPOPUP_POS command;HELP_SETWINPOS command;HELP_TCARD command;HELP_WM_HELP command;pop-up windows;pop-up windows, calling from a program;reference;reference, WinHelp APIs;WinHelp API;WinHelp API, described;WinHelp function}
\b\fs24 WinHelp
\par \pard\keepn\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \fs16 BOOL WinHelp(\plain\f1\fs16 HWND hwnd\b ,\plain\f1\fs16  LPCTSTR lpszHelpFile\b , \plain\f1\fs16 UINT fuCommand\b , \plain\f1\fs16 DWORD dwData\b )\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 The \b WinHelp\plain\f1\fs16  function starts Windows Help (WINHELP.EXE) and passes additional data indicating the nature of the help requested by the program.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\brdrb\brdrs\tx1435 \b Parameter\tab Description\plain\f1\fs16 
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 hwnd\tab Handle of the window requesting Help. The \b WinHelp\plain\f1\fs16  function uses this handle to keep track of which programs have requested Help. If fuCommand specifies HELP_CONTEXTMENU or HELP_WM_HELP, hwnd identifies the control requesting Help.
\par lpszHelpFile\tab Address of a null-terminated string containing the path, if necessary, and the name of the Help file that WinHelp is to display.
\par \tab The filename may be followed by an angle bracket (>) and the name of a secondary window if the topic is to be displayed in a secondary window rather than in the primary window. The name of the secondary window must have been defined previously in the \b [WINDOWS]\plain\f1\fs16  section of the Help Project (.HPJ) file.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li1435\ri125\fi-1305\tx1435 fuCommand\tab Type of help requested. For a list of possible values and how they affect the value to place in the dwData parameter, see the Comments section.
\par dwData\tab Additional data. The value used depends on the value of the fuCommand parameter. For a list of possible values, see the Comments section.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \b Return Value
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \plain\f1\fs16 If successful, the return value is TRUE; otherwise, it is FALSE.
\par \pard\sb115\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \b Comments
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 \plain\f1\fs16 The program specifies the name and, where required, the directory path of the Help file to display.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 Before closing the window that requested Help, the program must call \b WinHelp\plain\f1\fs16  with the fuCommand parameter set to HELP_QUIT. Until all programs have done this, WinHelp will not terminate. Note that calling WinHelp with the HELP_QUIT command is not necessary if you used the HELP_CONTEXTPOPUP command to start Help.
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125\tx1435 The following table shows the possible values for the fuCommand parameter and the corresponding formats of the dwData parameter: 
\par \trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \b fuCommand\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Action\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 dwData\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 \plain\f1\fs16 HELP_COMMAND\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Runs a Help macro or macro string. \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Address of a string that specifies the name of the Help macro(s) to run. If the string specifies multiple macro names, the names must be separated by colons or semicolons . You must use the short form of the macro name for some macros because WinHelp does not support the long name.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_CONTENTS\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the topic specified by the Contents option in the \b [OPTIONS]\plain\f1\fs16  section of the .HPJ file. This command is for backward compatibility. New programs should provide a .CNT file and use the HELP_FINDER command.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Ignored; set to 0.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_CONTEXT\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the topic identified by the specified context identifier defined in the \b [MAP]\plain\f1\fs16  section of the .HPJ file. \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Unsigned long integer containing the context identifier for the topic.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_CONTEXTMENU\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the Help menu for the selected window, and then displays (in a pop-up window) the topic for the selected control.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Address of an array of double word pairs. The first double word in each pair is a control identifier, and the second is a context number for a topic.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_CONTEXTPOPUP\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays, in a pop-up window, the topic identified by the specified context identifier defined in the \b [MAP]\plain\f1\fs16  section of the .HPJ file.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Unsigned long integer containing the context identifier for a topic.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_FINDER\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the Help Topics dialog box.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Ignored; set to 0.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_FORCEFILE\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Ensures that \b WinHelp\plain\f1\fs16  is displaying the correct Help file. If the incorrect Help file is being displayed, \b WinHelp\plain\f1\fs16  opens the correct one; otherwise, there is no action. \cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Ignored; set to 0.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_HELPONHELP\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays Help on how to use WinHelp, if the \b WINHLP32.HLP\plain\f1\fs16  file is available.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Ignored; set to 0.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_INDEX\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the topic specified by the \b CONTENTS\plain\f1\fs16  option in the \b [OPTIONS]\plain\f1\fs16  section of the .HPJ file. This command is for backward compatibility. New programs should provide a .CNT file and use the HELP_FINDER command.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Ignored; set to 0.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_KEY\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the topic in the keyword table that matches the specified keyword, if there is an exact match. If there is more than one match, this command displays the Topics Found list box.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Address of a keyword string. Multiple keywords must be separated by semi-colons.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_MULTIKEY\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the topic specified by a keyword in an alternative keyword table.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Address of a \b MULTIKEYHELP\plain\f1\fs16  structure that specifies a table footnote character and a keyword. \cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_PARTIALKEY\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the topic in the keyword table that matches the specified keyword if there is an exact match. If there is more than one match, this command displays the Topics Found dialog box. To display the Index without passing a keyword, you should use a pointer to an empty string.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Address of a keyword  string. Multiple keywords must be separated by semi-colons.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_QUIT\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Informs the WinHelp program that it is no longer needed. If no other programs have asked for Help, Windows closes the WinHelp program.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Ignored; set to 0.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_SETCONTENTS\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Specifies the Contents topic. The WinHelp program displays this topic when the user clicks the Contents button if the Help file does not have an associated .CNT file.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Unsigned long integer containing the context identifier for the Contents topic.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_SETPOPUP_POS\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Sets the position of the subsequent pop-up window.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Address of a \b POINTS\plain\f1\fs16  structure. The pop-up window is positioned as if the mouse cursor were at the specified point when the pop-up window is invoked.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_SETWINPOS\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays the Help window, if it is minimized or in memory, and sets its size and position as specified.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Address of a \b HELPWININFO\plain\f1\fs16  structure that specifies the size and position of either a primary or secondary Help window. \cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_TCARD\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Indicates that a command is for a training card instance of the WinHelp program. A program combines the HELP_TCARD flag with other commands by using the bitwise OR operator.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Depends on the command with which the flag is combined.\cell\intbl\row
\trowd\trgaph-5\trleft-6 \cellx2065\cellx4765\cellx7735\pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 HELP_WM_HELP\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Displays, in a pop-up window, the topic for the control identified by hwnd.\cell\pard \pard\intbl\sb75\sl-235\li115\ri125 Address of an array of double word pairs. The first double word in each pair is a control identifier, and the second is a context identifier for a topic.\cell\intbl\row
